      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "You are likely arching excessively because you are driving the bar only with your shins instead of your floor and hips, which isolates your lower back while neglecting your posterior chain. Ensure your forearms stay locked vertical to the shins during the pull to activate your glutes and hamstrings as they should. Additionally, focus on pushing the floor away with your entire back and legs rather than just kicking up from your shins to prevent back strain.",
      "source": "target",
