      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That rounding at the bottom is likely due to incorrect bracing; you need to engage your core to create an \"arch\" or rigid cylinder so your spine stays neutral while the bar leaves the floor. If your back feels weak here, focus on tightening your abs as if bracing for a punch rather than relying on external resistance. Properly loading your lower back will prevent that roundness and ensure your glutes and hamstrings feel stronger under the load.",
